title: Chilling Adventures of Sabrina Ending Explained, Missed Details, and Episode 10 Breakdown!
author: Think Story
comment: Dr. Cerberus also says he is the "oldest of three boys" when Hilda asks if he is a first born son. Probably a reference to Cerberus having three heads.
Not hearing Salem speak could be them playing with Sabrina's Mortal side. Like now that she's a full on witch we'll maybe be able to hear him

My biggest question, is Dorthea a legitimate ghost that came to guide her niece Susie? OR is she some demonic apparition that haunts her as a result of touching her possessed uncle? OR is she a ploy from Madam Satan to ultimately reveal that Sabrina is a witch?

I think Nick is the Devil or the Devil's son to try and seduce Sabrina to eventually get her to submit to him. It makes the most sense as to why he is so supportive of Sabrina and tries so hard to please her
